headline: Honda to Buy Ohio Battery Plant Assets From LGES for $2.9B
summary: HMC is set to buy Ohio battery plant building assets from LG Energy Solution for about $2.9 billion, aiming to boost efficiency at its JV ahead of 2025 operations.

headline: Tesla Under Scrutiny Due to Model 3 Door Release Concerns
summary: TSLA faces an NHTSA probe into Model 3 door releases, with claims that emergency controls are hidden, unlabeled, and difficult to find in critical situations.

headline: 2025: The year the Big 3 backed away from EVs
summary: The Big Three automakers — Ford, GM, and Stellantis —  have been caught in the crosshairs of a demand slump as they move away from massive EV investments and strategies, possibly leaving themselves on the back foot if EV demand increases.

headline: Tesla Stock Up 120% in Past 5 Years
summary: Tesla stock recently reached an all-time high on prospects for the company becoming a leader in self-driving taxis and robotics.
